reviewText: Not glamorized at all, a real look at three cattle-ranching families and how they do what they do every day.  Pretty gritty, lots of calving and trying to save the little guys when they're having trouble being born, etc.  Three very different ways of handling cattle on the ground - from modern to do-it-all-yourself old school.I really enjoy it because I love horses and looking at a lifestyle that uses them as the great animals they are for getting your work done will always have my full attention.  Makes ya wonder why someone would choose to ranch in Montana though!  LOL!
summary: If you like the true Cowboy stuff, this is it

reviewText: We missed seeing the series on Animal Planet and after reading the mostly positive reviews, I decided to surprise my husband with this selection as his relatives owned ranches in Nebraska and Montana.  The scenery is just breathtaking.  The families' stories are inspiring, informative, and a reminder that they indeed are carrying on a generational business and lifestyle that the majority of us wouldn't choose to (or could) exist in.We would highly recommend this 2-disc presentation to add to your western collection and plan on seeing it again...and again.

reviewText: I dislike reality TV because the participants generally have no redeeming characteristics, This show is different. It chronicles a year in the lives of three ranches in Montana. Two are run by families and the third, while family owned, was so large it was managed by family but worked by employees. It shows true American values of hard work and perseverance. For those of us who have always wanted to live on a ranch this series is some form of wish fulfillment. The only minus: they didn't make a second season.

reviewText: I loved seeing the process of of raising cows and the real decisions that come up during a year.Now, the only issue is the same issue I have with any "reality show" but since this was more real life it was not as bad.  There is, for some reason, a need to instill as much drama as possible in every aspect of reality shows now.  Every step of the year the narrator throws in your face that "this decision could cost this family their ranch" it was getting more than a little annoying.  In fact, instead of making a sense of drama, my wife and I made fun of each and every mention of this exact line, and it pulled us out of the episode each time.
summary: Great show, narration got a little old fast.
